# The vendored Lua read-only patch is applied (via `git apply`) against the LF
# source extracted from the upstream tarball. On Windows, git's autocrlf would
# check the patch out as CRLF, so its context lines no longer match the LF
# source and `git apply` fails ("patch does not apply"). Pin it — and the POSIX
# build scripts — to LF everywhere.
*.patch text eol=lf
*.sh    text eol=lf
